Terminalia (
Fig. 7 A-C
): Tergite VI brown and segment VII+VIII brownish black with silver pruinosity. Surstyili in lateral view narrow, less than 2 x the maximum cerci width; triangular shaped, narrow at the apex. Surstyli in posterior view without an expansion laterally. Apex of the hypandrium directed backwards. Middle bar subequal to the total length of the granular structure of distiphallus. Apex of distiphallus not curved.
